Slide 7 ‚Äì Image Forensics Engine
Core Forensics Modules

1Ô∏è‚É£ Error Level Analysis (ELA)

Detects recompression differences

Highlights edited regions

2Ô∏è‚É£ Noise Pattern Analysis

Identifies irregular noise caused by edits

3Ô∏è‚É£ Compression Artifact Analysis

Detects partial recompression in documents

4Ô∏è‚É£ Font & Layout Consistency Check

Detects font-size and alignment mismatches

5Ô∏è‚É£ Metadata Analysis

Checks PDF author, producer, timestamps

Identifies editing tools like Photoshop/Canva

Slide 8 ‚Äì Machine Learning Component
ML Role in the System

ML is used as a supporting signal, not the sole decision-maker

Trained on synthetic genuine and tampered documents

Learns patterns from forensic features

ML Output

Probability score indicating likelihood of manipulation

Combined with forensic score for final decision

